  "frame_version": "v4 -- 4th extraction bug fixed, oraios-serena excluded (supersedes v3, commit c88a74b)",
  "frame_status": "PROVISIONAL -- PAUSED, AWAITING GG DIRECTION (see pause_rationale)",
  "frame_status_note": "v3 was ratified 2026-07-04. Preparing the GG-redirected batch-1 trial target (oraios-serena) surfaced a 4th confirmed extraction bug (decorator STRING ARGUMENTS, not just decorator names, were matched for the substring 'tool' -- e.g. a Flask route path '/get_tool_stats' or a Click CLI flag '--tool-timeout' -- false-positiving as tool-registration decorators). Fixed with a regression test. Investigating oraios-serena further revealed its REAL tool architecture is CLASS-BASED (class ExecuteShellCommandTool(Tool, ...): ...), a third major registration paradigm this extractor does not support at all -- excluded as extraction_failed (not scored at either its old 37.3 or new 86.5-from-1-tool value, both untrustworthy).",
  "pause_rationale": "This is the 4th confirmed extraction bug and 2nd consecutive invalidated trial candidate found in one session, each ONLY surfaced by deep-diving the SPECIFIC server selected next for the trial batch. After this correction, the near_empty tier's WORST member has 85.7% description coverage -- there is NO server left in the 21-server scoreable pool with less than 57.1% description coverage. This is an extremely strong result, arguably implausibly strong given general knowledge that thin/name-only tool descriptions are a widely reported real-world MCP pain point. Given the demonstrated pattern (every server investigated in depth so far revealed a NEW, previously undetected extraction gap), there is low confidence the remaining pool is free of similar undetected issues. Recommend NOT selecting another trial candidate reactively -- either a systematic audit of the remaining pool, or an explicit acknowledgment of mechanical-extraction limits, is warranted before further prevalence claims or trial execution.",
  "bug_fixes_this_version": [
    {
      "id": "decorator_string_argument_false_positive",
      "affected": [
        "oraios-serena (led to full exclusion, see below)"
      ],
      "minor_blast_radius": [
        "stickerdaniel-linkedin-mcp-server (18->17 tools, composite unchanged 94.2)",
        "taylorwilsdon-google_workspace_mcp (118->116 tools, composite 96.4->96.6)",
        "lucasastorian-llmwiki (13->12 tools, composite 78.1->80.0)",
        "mrexodia-ida-pro-mcp (92->90 tools, composite 79.5->80.0)"
      ],
      "summary": "_has_tool_decorator checked the substring 'tool' against the FULL unparsed decorator text (ast.unparse(dec)), including string literal ARGUMENTS -- not just the decorator's own called name. A Flask route @app.route('/get_tool_stats') or a Click CLI flag @click.option('--tool-timeout', ...) both contain 'tool' inside a string argument and were mistaken for tool-registration decorators. Fixed: check ONLY the decorator's called name (attribute or bare name), never its full unparsed text or string arguments."
    }
  ],
